name: Instant Pot® Vegetarian Cabbage Soup
author: sashman
summary: Bursting with cabbage, green beans, and lots of other vegetables, this vegetarian soup is easy to make in the Instant Pot®.
ingredients: 1 (15 ounce) can diced tomatoes with basil, garlic, and oregano, undrained
1 (15 ounce) can no-salt-added diced tomatoes, undrained
directions: Turn on a multi-functional pressure cooker (such as Instant Pot®) and select Saute function
Allow pot to heat for 3 minutes
Add oil, then add onion, carrots, celery, and garlic
Cook, stirring often, until vegetables are slightly softened, about 6 minutes
Stir in cabbage, green beans, and salt
Add vegetable stock and both cans of tomatoes with their juices
Select high pressure according to manufacturer's instructions; set timer for 15 minutes
Allow 10 to 15 minutes for pressure to build
Release pressure using the natural-release method according to manufacturer's instructions, 10 to 40 minutes
Remove the lid and stir in dill and parsley
